<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17510703-8">
               <interp inst="t17510703-8" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510703-8" type="year" value="1751"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510703-8" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17510703"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510703-8" type="date" value="17510703"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17510703-8-off34-c65" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510703-8-defend81 t17510703-8-off34 t17510703-8-verdict38"></join>
         
               <p>416. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17510703-8-defend81" type="defendantName">
                     Lawrence 
                     Cox 
                  <interp inst="t17510703-8-defend81" type="surname" value="Cox"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-defend81" type="given" value="Lawrence"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-defend81" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17510703-8-off34" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-off34" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-off34" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one silver spoon, value 5 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17510703-8-victim83" type="victimName">
                     Francis 
                     Wilson 
                  <interp inst="t17510703-8-victim83" type="surname" value="Wilson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-victim83" type="given" value="Francis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-victim83" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510703-8-off34 t17510703-8-victim83"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17510703-8-cd35" type="crimeDate">June 22</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510703-8-off34 t17510703-8-cd35"></join>. ||</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510703-8-person84">
                  Thomas 
                  Jones 
               <interp inst="t17510703-8-person84" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person84" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person84" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. 
               <persName id="t17510703-8-person85">
                  Francis 
                  Wilson 
               <interp inst="t17510703-8-person85" type="surname" value="Wilson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person85" type="given" value="Francis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person85" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , at <placeName id="t17510703-8-crimeloc36">Charing-Cross</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17510703-8-crimeloc36" type="placeName" value="Charing-Cross"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17510703-8-crimeloc36" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510703-8-off34 t17510703-8-crimeloc36"></join>: the prisoner is a <rs id="t17510703-8-deflabel37" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510703-8-defend81 t17510703-8-deflabel37"></join>, I had sent him for two brooms the 22d of June, he had been in the house. After he had been gone about two hours he was stop'd offering the silver spoon to sale.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510703-8-person86">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Chandler 
               <interp inst="t17510703-8-person86" type="surname" value="Chandler"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person86" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person86" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was in our kitchen the 22d of last month, the spoons were all there the Friday night, and one of them was missing on Saturday about ten o'clock.</p>
               <p>The spoon was produced in court broke in two pieces, and deposed to by the two witnesses.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510703-8-person87">
                  William 
                  Lynch 
               <interp inst="t17510703-8-person87" type="surname" value="Lynch"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person87" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-person87" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I cry old cloaths about the streets: coming up the Strand the 22d of last month the prisoner call'd me into a court, and said, let us see if you and I can bargain, and shew'd me the spoon, saying, he found it the morning before in St. Jame's-street. Seeing it in this condition, bent and broke, I thought he could not come honestly by it, so took him to the constable. He was taken before the Justice, and Mr. Wilson came and proved it his property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I ask a thousand pardons. I never did such a thing in my life before.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17510703-8-verdict38" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-verdict38" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17510703-8-punish39" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-punish39" type="punishmentCategory" value="miscPunish"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510703-8-punish39" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="branding"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510703-8-defend81 t17510703-8-punish39"></join>
               
                     <note>[Branding. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
